# Core render-surface coverage: headings, ul/ol lists, a table, <progress>,
# a <pre><raw> code block, a card (div.card), and a link -- one fixture
# walking the element set docs/architecture.md and term.go both describe.
# Every id here names a BLOCK-level element, so each gets an Expect Box;
# li/td/tr rows do not (they render through the list/table path, which
# does not record per-item boxes -- docs/ctml.md S:S14).

Source elements.ctml
Set Width 80

Expect Text "Coverage Elements"
Expect Box page-title

Expect Text "Apple"
Expect Text "Banana"
Expect Text "Cherry"
Expect Box fruit-list

Expect Text "First step"
Expect Text "Second step"
Expect Box steps-list

Expect Text "Basic"
Expect Text "Pro"
Expect Box pricing-table

Expect Text "65%"
Expect Box upload-progress

Expect Text "func main"
Expect Box code-block

Expect Text "Feature title"
Expect Text "Feature description text"
Expect Box feature-card

Expect Text "the docs"
Expect Box link-paragraph

Expect Fits
